    "body": "### Problem\n\nI installed neovim with brew and get the following error when closing nvim: `E886: Failed to create directory /Users/{my-user}/.local/state/nvim for writing Sha Da file: permission denied`. Re-install also didn't work.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nInstalled neovim with brew (`brew install neovim`).\r\nOpened neovim with `nvim`.\r\nClosing with `:q`\r\nGetting the error: `E886: Failed to create directory /Users/{my-user}/.local/state/nvim for writing Sha Da file: permission denied`\r\n\r\n<img width=\"857\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-06-06 at 21 08 06\" src=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/48725618/f0cfb19f-c299-4548-ba9f-6d0a47070c03\">\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nRun `:q`\r\nClosing nvim\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nstable 0.10.0 (bottled), HEAD\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, version 9.0.2142\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nSonoma 14.5\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nTerminal 2.14 (453)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nzsh: command not found: xterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbrew install neovim",
